This paper deals with list decoding algorithms for error-correcting codes, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories in computer science. The use of rational interpolation and Grobner bases suggests that the paper may belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-categories. The mention of GRS codes and Goppa codes suggests that the paper may also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) or Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Finally, the mention of a connection between the Wu algorithm and the Guruswami-Sudan algorithm suggests that the paper may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
